cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.OH, cs.MM

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the convergence of wireless and wired services in a passive optical network, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper evaluates the performance of different waveforms in terms of channel spacing, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the convergence of wireless and wired services in a network, which is a topic covered under communications and networking. 
4. cs.OH (Other Computer Science) - The paper may also fall under the category of other computer science as it deals with the convergence of different technologies. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the transmission of different waveforms over a fibre network, which may fall under the domain of multimedia.
